<h3>How to use:</h3>
<p>First, apply base styling to prep element for transition.</p>
{{ '```scss
.class {
  @include bolt-transition--fade-in($base: true);
}
```' | markdown }}
<p>Next, apply the same mixin with <code>$base: true</code> to the css.</p>
<p>For example, to trigger the transition on hover...</p>
{{ '```scss
.class {
  @include bolt-transition--fade-in($base: true);
  &:hover {
    @include bolt-transition--fade-in($active: true);
  }
}
```' | markdown }}
<p>Additionally, transitions can be tied to data attributes that are applied with the javascript transition utilities provided through <code>@bolt/animations</code>.</p>
{{ '```scss
.class {
  @include bolt-transition--fade-in($base: true);
  &[data-anim-triggered="yes"] {
    @include bolt-transition--fade-in($active: true);
  }
}
```' | markdown }}

